      <p>
        <s>The given scene is taken from the film <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="title">The Hate U Give</ref> by <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="director">George Tillmann Jr.</ref> and released in <date>2018</date>.</s>
        <s>It's about <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr's</ref> relationship with her boyfriend, who did a big mistake in the past.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>The scene <choice><orig>beginns</orig><reg>begins</reg></choice> with <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Chris</ref> walking down the hallway of his and <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr's</ref> school.</s>
        <s>He notices <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref> and goes directly to her.</s>
        <s>Afterwards he <choice><orig>present's</orig><reg>presents</reg></choice> his self made beat to <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref> with putting his headphones over her ears.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref><choice><orig>react's</orig><reg>reacts</reg></choice> mad because <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Chris</ref> did a big mistake in the past.</s>
        <s>Additionally <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Chris</ref> doesn't know how to make <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref> forgive him so he <choice><orig>start's</orig><reg>starts</reg></choice> speaking about his beat and dances to it, which in the end made her laugh.</s>
      </p>
